.\" kilonode/docs/man/kilonode-user.1
.Dd May 26, 2026
.Dt KILONODE-USER 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm kilonode-user
.Nd manage local KiloNode BBS users and read state
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Fl -store Ar path
.Ar command
.Op Ar arguments
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
manages KiloNode-native local BBS user records and per-user read-state files.
It does not manage passwords.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl -store Ar path
Use the message store rooted at
.Ar path .
.It Fl -help
Show command usage.
.El
.Sh COMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Cm init
Initialize user and read-state directories.
.It Cm create Ar callsign
Create a user.
.It Cm show Ar callsign
Show one user.
.It Cm list
List users.
.It Cm seen Ar callsign
Update last-seen and login counters.
.It Cm disable Ar callsign
Disable a user.
.It Cm enable Ar callsign
Enable a user.
.It Cm mark-read Ar callsign Ar id
Mark a message read.
.It Cm is-read Ar callsign Ar id
Check read state.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Pa var/messages/users
User records.
.It Pa var/messages/read
Read-state files.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
.Dl kilonode-user --store /tmp/kilonode-msg-test create M6VPN-1
.Dl kilonode-user --store /tmp/kilonode-msg-test list
.Sh SECURITY NOTES
Passwords and authentication are deferred. Local filesystem permissions are the
main protection for user files in this pass.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr kilonode-msg 1 ,
.Xr kilonode-store 1
.Sh AUTHORS
KiloNode is developed by M6VPN.
